<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  The interaction-group catalog. Each <PawnDiary.DiaryInteractionGroupDef> is one themed
  bucket of events with an enable-by-default flag and a diary-prompt instruction. RimWorld
  loads this at startup; edit it and restart the game to add/retune groups or reword prompts
  WITHOUT recompiling the C# (see DiaryInteractionGroupDef in InteractionGroups.cs).

  Fields:
    defName        - stable key (also the key player settings save overrides under; don't rename)
    label          - name shown in mod settings
    order          - lower numbers are classified first ("first match wins"); catch-all highest
    domain         - Interaction (matches InteractionDefs), MentalState (matches MentalStateDefs),
                     or Tale (matches TaleDefs from RimWorld's notable-history system)
    defaultEnabled - whether events in this group are recorded by default
    important      - whether entries in this group get the strong importance marker in the Diary tab
    combat         - whether events in this group are combat-related (adds the equipped weapon to the prompt)
    batch          - optional Interaction-domain batching policy:
                     enabled, windowTicks, maxEvents, scope (Pair or Def), syntheticDefName,
                     labelKey, briefKey, headerKey, fallbackKey, instructionKey,
                     includeInteractionLabel
    instruction    - the diary-prompt instruction shared by every event in the group
    matchDefNames  - exact interaction/mental-state defNames this group claims (case-insensitive)
    matchTokens    - substrings; a defName containing any token (case-insensitive) is claimed
    catchAll       - true = matches everything in its domain (leave matchers empty)
-->
